quran[25]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,52,"who would say, ‘Can it be that you<sup>sg </sup>are really of those who believe?"
  37,53,"Can it be thatwhen we have died and become dust and bones, can it be that{1}we will really be called to account?’”",1:[Qira’at: Nafie’, Al-Kesa’i and Ya’qub read it as: “Can it be that when we have died and become dust and bones we will really be called to account?” Ibn Amer and Abu Ja’far read it as: “When we have died and become dust and bones, can it be that we will really be called to account?”]
  37,54,"He said<i>(to his companions in Paradise) </i>, “Can you<sup>pl </sup>view<i>(him) </i>?”"
  37,55,"Then he viewed<i>(him) </i>and saw him in the midst of purgatory."
  37,56,"He said,<i>“(I swear) </i>by Allah, you<sup>sg </sup>almost ruined me."
  37,57,"And were it not for the blessing of my Lord, I would have been of the arraigned.”"
  37,58,"“Are we<i>(then) </i>not to die"
  37,59,"except for our first death? And are we never to be punished?”"
  37,60,"It is most surely this which is the great triumph."
  37,61,"For the like of this let the workers work."
  37,62,"Is this a better hospitality or the Tree of Zaqqum{1}?",1:[Trees in Hell which produce hot, bitter, rotten fruit.]
  37,63,"Indeed, We have made it a means of trial for the unjust."
  37,64,"Indeed, it is a tree that comes out from the very origin of purgatory."
  37,65,"Its yield is as if it were devils’ heads."
  37,66,"So they are sure to eat from it and fill their bellies with it."
  37,67,"Then, on top of it, they will have a brew of scalding water."
  37,68,"Then their return is sure to be to purgatory."
  37,69,"Indeed, they found their forefathers astray,"
  37,70,"so they rush along in their footsteps."
  37,71,"And certainly, most of the ancients before them went astray."
  37,72,"And certainly, We sent among them forewarners."
  37,73,"So look<sup>sg </sup>at what the outcome was for those who were warned,"
  37,74,"except for Allah’s sincere chosen{1}servants.",1:[Qira’at: Ibn Kathir, Abu Amr, Ibn Amer and Ya’qub read it as: “…except for Allah’s sincere servants.”]
  37,75,"And certainly, Noah called out to Us, so the very excellent of responders are We!"
  37,76,"Thus We delivered him and his family from the great calamity,"
